Fresno.Robert E. Coyle United States Courthouse: The Robert E. Coyle United States Courthouse is a 9-story, 69 m (226 ft) high-rise completed in 2005 in downtown Fresno, California. The building is named after U.S. District Judge Robert Everett Coyle (1930–2012), and it is one of the tallest buildings in Downtown Fresno and Central California.
